LABEL: 0x4c

LABEL: 0x1be
JPN: 今日も見張っていたのか。
ENG: Guess she staked the place out again.

LABEL: 0x208
ENG: "Should I go grab one for you?"

LABEL: 0x280
JPN: 遠慮しているというより、もう信用できないという顔だ。
ENG: It felt less like she was being polite and more like she was doubting me.

LABEL: 0x2c4

ENG: I felt like I had to restore her faith in me.

LABEL: 0x2f2

LABEL: 0x468

JPN: 謎の俺の剣幕におされて、しろははやっと歩き出す。

ENG: "What are you going to do with it?"

JPN: 謎の着ぐるみを手に入れた

LABEL: 0xac4

LABEL: 0xaf8

LABEL: 0xb20

ENG: "Nobody'll know who you are if you wear this."

LABEL: 0xb58
ENG: "You can buy all the sweets you want."

JPN: しろはがまじまじと俺を見る。

LABEL: 0xc90

ENG: "We might scare the candy store lady, though."

LABEL: 0xcf8
JPN: 「おばーちゃん、あんまり気にしないんじゃないかな」
ENG: "I have a feeling she won't mind too much."

LABEL: 0xd44

LABEL: 0xdaa

LABEL: 0xf1a

LABEL: 0xf68

ENG: It'd be one thing in the city―she might attract a couple stares, and that'd be the end of it. Out in the countryside, though, it sort of felt weirdly realistic, like some bizarre cryptid was actually walking around in the street.

LABEL: 0xfe6
JPN: ……謎の着ぐるみがのこのこと、駄菓子屋に入っていく。
ENG: ...The unidentified animal costume nonchalantly strolled into the candy store.

LABEL: 0x102a
ENG: You don't see that every day.

NameJPN: 駄菓子屋のおばーちゃん

LABEL: 0x147c

ENG: "What does that mean? What's going on?"

ENG: "My pet Pekemon ran away, did'ja say?"

LABEL: 0x168e
JPN: 「おじいちゃん、ペケモン飼ってたの？」
ENG: "Grandpa, you were keeping a Pekemon as a pet?"

LABEL: 0x16ce
JPN: 「孫のゲーム手伝って、ゲットしてやったんや」
ENG: "I caught one when I was helpin' out with my grandson's game!"

LABEL: 0x171e
JPN: 「孫が悲しむ。ペケモンを返せ」
ENG: "My grandson will be heartbroken... Give me back my Pekemon!"

LABEL: 0x1760
JPN: 「わしのペケモンを捕まえてくれええ」

LABEL: 0x17fe
JPN: 大事になってしまった。
ENG: Things got out of hand incredibly quickly.

LABEL: 0x185a
JPN: 『そこのペケモン、何をしている』
ENG: "You, the Pekemon over there! What do you think you're doing!?"

LABEL: 0x18a2
JPN: 『お年寄りが驚くから、そんな姿でうろつくな』
ENG: "Stop loitering around in that outfit! You're scaring the elderly!"

LABEL: 0x1a1c
JPN: しろははどうなったんだろう。

LABEL: 0x1ac2
JPN: 「今日、ペケモンが現れたらしいです」
ENG: "Apparently, they found a wild Pekemon on the island today!"

LABEL: 0x1b0e
JPN: 「誰かに危害をくわえたとかはないけど、気を付けるようにって」
ENG: "Nobody was hurt or anything, but they told us to be careful anyway!"

LABEL: 0x1b72
JPN: 「見つけたら出来るだけ生け捕りにしてくださいって」
ENG: "Oh, and that if we do find it, we should do our best to capture it alive!"

LABEL: 0x1bee
JPN: 「田舎はへんな生き物がいるんですねぇ」
ENG: "There sure are some weird animals out here, aren't there?"

LABEL: 0x1c2c

ENG: It had turned into quite the rumor.

LABEL: 0x1cde

LABEL: 0x1d12

LABEL: 0x1d4a

ENG: I mean, surely she'd already made it home, right?

LABEL: 0x1e04

LABEL: 0x1ef4

LABEL: 0x1f18

LABEL: 0x1fe2
JPN: 「アイスの袋開けたら、溶けてた」
ENG: "But when I opened the popsicle, it was completely melted."

LABEL: 0x201c

ENG: She was holding a popsicle stick―all that remained of her watermelon bar.

LABEL: 0x211a
JPN: 「もう、こんな悲しい思いはしたくない」

LABEL: 0x216c
JPN: しろははそう言って去って行った。
ENG: That was all Shiroha had to say. She walked off.

LABEL: 0x21f2
JPN: 彼女が去った後には、さっきまで握っていたスイカバーの棒が落ちていた。
ENG: After she left, I noticed the stick she'd been holding lying on the ground.

LABEL: 0x2246
JPN: ぽつんと、取り残されたかつてスイカバーだったもの。
ENG: The last remains of what was once a watermelon bar.

LABEL: 0x2288
ENG: It lay there, discarded, bathed in the gentle moonlight.

LABEL: 0x22ac
JPN: どことなく哀愁が漂ってた。
ENG: The physical form of tragedy itself.
